en_129965_0	Former External Affairs Minister G.L. Pieris was summoned to the CID today in connection to a statement made over a suicide kit found in a house at Chavakachcheri, Jaffna.
en_129965_1	The former Minister arrived at the premises this morning accompanied by parliamentarians Wimal Weerawansa, C.B. Ratnayake, Dinesh Gunawardena, Pavithra Wanniarachchi as well as Namal Rajapaksa.
en_129965_2	Addressing a recent media briefing, the former Minister has stated that the discovered explosives were planned to be brought to Wellawatta area.
en_129965_3	He further noted that he was questioned with regard to this statement.
en_129965_4	Addressing the media former External Affairs Minister G.L. Pieris stated that the government has set aside investigations on matters affecting the security, and acting in a manner to suppress anti-government politicians.
en_129965_5	Expressing his views, MP Namal Rajapaksa stated that talking about the national security has posed a problem to the government.
